# Security — Never Violate

## Every PHP file
First executable line after <?php and namespace:
defined('ABSPATH') || exit;

## AJAX handlers
- check_ajax_referer() before any processing
- current_user_can() capability check always
- Never read $_POST/$_GET directly — sanitize first

## Sanitization by type
- Text: sanitize_text_field()
- Email: sanitize_email()
- Integer: absint()
- HTML: wp_kses_post()
- URL (save): esc_url_raw()

## Output escaping — always
- HTML: esc_html()
- Attributes: esc_attr()
- URLs: esc_url()
- JS: wp_json_encode()

## Database
- $wpdb->prepare() on every query with variable input — no exceptions
- No SQL string concatenation with user data

## Nonces
- Every form: wp_nonce_field('km_action', 'km_nonce')
- Every AJAX: wp_create_nonce() on JS side, check_ajax_referer() on PHP side

## Forbidden
- No eval()
- No base64_decode() on dynamic data
- No direct file includes without ABSPATH check